@athiranair2000 thanks a lot for sending this MR :)

As you notice, the text seems to jump out of the decoration box when the error is shown. 
It seems to be an issue with flutter itself, though I'm not very sure. 
A workaround I thought of is to increase the size of the input box so that even if the text jumps up, it will stay inside the box and therefore not look half inside and half outside the box.

@padth4i @immadisairaj If you know of any better fix for this please mention.

@Chromicle @immadisairaj @athiranair2000 IMO even after increasing the size, the UI will look a bit odd. 
I say since we're using a box to wrap text around, instead of using the errorText approach directly/through a validator, we can show a toast instead.

That will keep our UI neat and show a user a notification as well.
